<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><magicdraw><class classType="Class" humanType="Class" icon="index_files/icon_class_1555793073.jpg" id="_9_5_f720368_1110473546784_913090_10473"><documentation humanName="Documentation" mode="standard">A class to perform rendering of the glyphs.
This can be implemented to be stateless, or
to hold some information as a cache to
facilitate faster rendering and model/view
translation.  At a minimum, the GlyphPainter
allows a View implementation to perform its
duties independent of a particular version
of JVM and selection of capabilities (i.e.
shaping for i18n, etc).
&lt;p&gt;
This implementation is intended for operation
under the JDK.  It uses the
java.awt.font.TextLayout class to do i18n capable
rendering.

@author  Timothy Prinzing
@version 1.21 06/28/04
@see GlyphView
